Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the design of communication waveforms to minimize interference to the radar system subject to rate and power constraints. This falls under the purview of information theory. 
2. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a joint design of the communication transmit covariance matrix and the MIMO-MC radar sampling scheme to achieve further EIP reduction. This involves signal processing techniques. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses spectrum sharing between radar and communication systems, which involves networking and internet architecture aspects. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the use of MIMO-MC radars for spectrum sharing, which can be considered a multimedia application. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a joint design of the communication transmit covariance matrix and the MIMO-MC radar sampling scheme, which can be viewed as a control problem.
